# SaveFood — .cursorrules
# Expert ASP.NET Core 8 Backend Rules for AI Coding Agents
# ============================================================
# READ THIS ENTIRELY BEFORE GENERATING ANY CODE.
# These rules are ABSOLUTE. Deviation is NOT allowed unless the user explicitly overrides.

## IDENTITY
You are an Expert .NET 8 Backend Engineer working on SaveFood — a web marketplace for near-expiry food.
Tech: ASP.NET Core 8, C# 12, SQL Server, Entity Framework Core 8, deployed on Render via Docker.

---

## ARCHITECTURE (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

- Pattern: N-Tier + Repository Pattern
- Flow: Controller → Service → Repository → DbContext
- NEVER put business logic in Controllers
- NEVER call DbContext directly outside Repository classes
- NEVER expose EF entities directly from API endpoints — always use DTOs
- ONE DbContext (SaveFoodDbContext), registered as Scoped
- ALL async — never use .Result or .Wait()
- Global Exception Handling Middleware handles ALL unhandled exceptions
- ALWAYS define an I{Name} interface before any Repository or Service implementation

---

## PROJECT STRUCTURE

```
src/SaveFood.API/          → Controllers, Middleware, Extensions, Program.cs
src/SaveFood.Application/  → DTOs, Interfaces, Services, Validators, Mappings, Common
src/SaveFood.Domain/       → Entities, Enums, Constants
src/SaveFood.Infrastructure/ → Data (DbContext, Config, Migrations), Repositories, Services, Jobs
```

Project references: API → Application + Infrastructure; Infrastructure → Application + Domain; Application → Domain

---

## ENTITIES & ENUMS

All entities inherit BaseEntity (Id: Guid, CreatedAt, UpdatedAt, IsDeleted: bool).
SOFT DELETE ONLY — never DELETE rows, set IsDeleted = true.
Global query filters on DbContext exclude IsDeleted = true for Product, Order, Store.

Key entities: ApplicationUser, Store, Product, Order, OrderItem, RefreshToken
Enums: ProductStatus (Active, Expired, SoldOut, Removed), OrderStatus (Pending, Confirmed, Preparing, Delivered, Cancelled), UserRole (Admin, StoreOwner, Customer)

ApplicationUser : IdentityUser<Guid> — adds FullName, AvatarUrl, Role (UserRole enum), StoreId (Guid?)

---

## DTO RULES

- Request DTOs: suffix "Request" (e.g. CreateProductRequest)  
- Response DTOs: suffix "Response" (e.g. ProductResponse)
- Use C# records for immutable DTOs
- NO nested EF entity objects — flatten or use dedicated nested response DTOs
- AutoMapper handles ALL Entity↔DTO mapping — never write manual new DTO { ... } blocks
- AutoMapper profiles live in Application/Mappings/

---

## VALIDATION

- FluentValidation for ALL request DTOs (never DataAnnotations on DTOs)
- Validators in Application/Validators/
- Register: builder.Services.AddValidatorsFromAssemblyContaining<T>() + AddFluentValidationAutoValidation()
- Always validate: ExpiryDate > UtcNow, DiscountedPrice < OriginalPrice, positive quantities

---

## AUTHENTICATION

- ASP.NET Core Identity + JWT Bearer
- Refresh tokens stored in DB (RefreshToken entity), hashed with HMACSHA512
- Google OAuth: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.Google
- Facebook OAuth: Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.Facebook
- JWT claims MUST include: userId, email, fullName, storeId, roles
- ClockSkew = TimeSpan.Zero (no tolerance for expired tokens)
- SignalR: read JWT from query string "access_token" for hub connections

Role-based auth:
- [Authorize(Roles = "Admin")] for admin endpoints
- [Authorize(Roles = "StoreOwner,Admin")] for product/store management
- [Authorize(Roles = "Customer")] for placing orders
- [Authorize] for authenticated-only (any role)

---

## GLOBAL EXCEPTION HANDLING

GlobalExceptionMiddleware maps exceptions to HTTP responses:
- SecurityTokenExpiredException → 401, code: TOKEN_EXPIRED
- UnauthorizedAccessException → 403, code: FORBIDDEN
- ProductExpiredException → 422, code: PRODUCT_EXPIRED
- InsufficientStockException → 422, code: OUT_OF_STOCK
- NotFoundException → 404, code: NOT_FOUND
- ValidationException → 400, code: VALIDATION_ERROR
- All others → 500, code: SERVER_ERROR

Custom exceptions live in Application/Common/Exceptions/
Response format: { code: string, message: string, timestamp: DateTime }

---

## BACKGROUND JOBS (HANGFIRE)

- ProductExpiryJob: runs every 30 minutes ("*/30 * * * *")
  - Queries products where ExpiryDate <= UtcNow and Status == Active
  - Sets Status = ProductStatus.Expired
  - Notifies store owner via SignalR: hub.Clients.Group("store-{storeId}").SendAsync("ProductExpired", ...)
- LowStockNotificationJob: runs every hour
  - Notifies stores when StockQuantity <= 5
- Hangfire dashboard at /hangfire, protected by HangfireAdminFilter (Admin role only)
- Storage: Hangfire.SqlServer (same connection string)

---

## SIGNALR NOTIFICATIONS

Hub: NotificationHub (requires [Authorize])
OnConnectedAsync: add user to groups "store-{storeId}" (if StoreOwner) and "user-{userId}"
Events to implement: OrderPlaced, OrderStatusChanged, ProductExpired, LowStock

---

## VNPAY PAYMENT

- VNPayService implements IVNPayService
- CreatePaymentUrl: builds sorted query params + HMAC-SHA512 signature
- ProcessCallback: validates HMAC-SHA512 + checks vnp_ResponseCode == "00"
- Amount in VNPay = actual amount × 100 (integer, no decimals)
- Timestamp format: yyyyMMddHHmmss in GMT+7
- PaymentController: POST /api/payment/create-vnpay/{orderId}, GET /api/payment/vnpay-return

---

