## CODING CONVENTIONS

- PascalCase: classes, methods, properties, enums
- camelCase: local variables, parameters
- _camelCase: private instance fields
- Use nameof() instead of magic strings for property names
- Every async repository/service method MUST accept CancellationToken ct = default
- All list endpoints return PaginatedList<T> (PageNumber, PageSize, TotalCount, Items)
- All API responses wrapped in ApiResponse<T> { bool Success, string Message, T? Data }
- Logging: Serilog only via ILogger<T>; Information for business events, Error for exceptions
- Never log sensitive data (passwords, tokens, payment secrets)

---

## RENDER DEPLOYMENT

- Dockerfile: multi-stage build (sdk:8.0 build → aspnet:8.0 runtime), EXPOSE 8080
- Apply EF migrations on startup: db.Database.MigrateAsync() inside scoped service
- All secrets via environment variables (NEVER hardcode): ConnectionStrings__DefaultConnection, Jwt__Key, VNPay__HashSecret, etc.
- ASPNETCORE_URLS=http://+:8080 (Render uses port 8080)

---

## DI REGISTRATION

All registrations in API/Extensions/ServiceCollectionExtensions.cs via extension methods.
Pattern: services.AddScoped<IInterface, Implementation>()
Never use concrete types directly in constructors — always inject interfaces.
